        Intuit is seeking a Director of Data Science to join our Innovation and Advanced Technology Group in Mountain View, CA.
        The Innovation team develops game changing technologies and experiments that redefine and disrupt our current product offerings. You'll be designing, building, iterating, and prototyping algorithms and applications on top of the collective financial data of 37 million consumers and small businesses. Applications will span multiple business lines, including personal finance, small business accounting, and tax.
        You thrive on ambiguity and enjoy the frequent pivoting that's part of the exploration. Your team will be very small – no bigger than two pizzas can feed – and team members frequently wear multiple hats.
        This leadership role involves close collaboration with the Intuit Data Science community, key decision makers within the product offerings, Innovation & Advanced Technology Group's engineering and design teams. This role ranges from deep science thought leader / mentor, consultative business facilitator, leading discussions, to research experimentalist to technology innovator. The individual must be comfortable partnering with core data infrastructure teams such as big data infrastructure, software, and data warehousing, as well as product and engineering management driving the business.
